liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Egypt's state-run media is reporting a convoy of 17 aid trucks has crossed the border into Gaza at Rafah, according to the Associated Press. Reuters previously reported that sources in Rafah said a convoy was being inspected before possibly entering the territory. A convoy of 20 trucks crossed into Gaza yesterday, carrying food, water and medical supplies. The UN says the first convoy was the equivalent of "about 4 per cent of the daily average of imports into Gaza prior to the hostilities".

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A spokesman for Gaza's Hamas-run health ministry says 4,651 Palestinians have died in Israeli strikes since the beginning of this latest round of conflict on October 7. The spokesman said 266 of those deaths had been recorded over the past 24 hours, with Israel significantly stepping up its bombardment of Gaza in preparation for a coming ground invasion. The spokesman also said more than 14,245 others have been wounded, with 70 per cent of those being women and children.
